Dear Hiring Team,

It is with great pleasure that I submit my candidacy for the *Software Engineer* role with *Zoom*. I bring professional experience building backend platforms, distributed systems, and agentic workflows, along with a Master of Science in Computer Science from Pace University.

At Sperse, I developed an MCP interaction layer that translates natural-language intents into safe, validated tool calls across *1000+ platform endpoints* in distributed systems, enabling enterprise-level backend services for global communication. I also built monitoring tools and metrics with Langfuse and LangSmith (tracing, structured logs, and evaluation hooks), driving data-informed improvements that reduced latency by *60%* and lowered API costs by *50%*. At Qualitest, I designed backend storage APIs and microservices across PostgreSQL, Redis, S3, Google Cloud Storage, and MinIO, and contributed to AWS-backed IAM services with Step Functions, Git, and CI/CD practices across cross-functional teams.

Zoom’s mission to help people connect, collaborate, and get more work done together strongly resonates with me, as does your AI-first work platform focus on human connection. I am equally aligned with your values of caring for customers and delivering happiness. I would bring that same mindset to your team through systems thinking, reliable cloud infrastructure and deployment strategies, and mentorship demonstrated through technical workshops delivered to *+50* students.

I would welcome the opportunity to contribute to Zoom’s collaboration platform and help build secure, high-performance backend systems for users worldwide. I would love to discuss my interest in this position with your team and can be reached at #ph or #eml. Thank you for your time and consideration, I look forward to connecting!

